summary:
Request from @moon-cake-cafe Zodiac: Sagittarius
 Birthday: November 29
 MBTI: INFP
 Favorite Animals: Jellyfish, Octopus,...
body:
Request from @moon-cake-cafe

Zodiac: Sagittarius

Birthday: November 29

MBTI: INFP

Favorite Animals: Jellyfish, Octopus, Tigers, and Dogs

Favorite Color: Red

Hobby: Drawing, collecting books, collecting snowglobes

Aspiration: To become a professional artist

Favorite type of area: The ocean’s pretty neat, but I also like to walk under trees when it’s fall; the colors are so nice!

Bad traits: Passive aggressive, unreliable, immature

Positive traits: Accepting, compassionate, passionate

I’ll do a team for you as well, since this one was pretty simple & I thought of a full team really quickly! 

Meet your Partner!

Growlithe! 

♡ Growlithe is a very loyal, reliable & direct Pokemon! It loves it’s trainer more than anything in the world, and will not think twice about fighting any person or Pokemon, no matter how strong they are, to defend it’s trainer. It can smell a threat from very far away. And I mean this literally! It can actually smell the emotional energy other life forms give off, so if there is hostility in it’s territory, it will be alerted instantly It can also be able to detect sadness or happiness in it’s loved ones, and will act accordingly. It’s a great support-Pokemon! 

♡ it’s been with humans for ages, so it is a very friendly Pokemon! As long as it does not sense hostility & someone is a familiar face, it will open up quite easily. Just tell Growlithe that a person or Pokemon is a friend, and it will let it’s heavy guards down without further thought. After this, it just becomes a playful puppy. 

♡ Growlithe won’t mind going to a beach, but don’t expect it to want to get wet! And being a fire type with soft & fluffy fur, it will be great for cuddling up with in cool autumn & winter weather. 

Other team members include:

I think the rest of your new buddies pretty much speak for themselves! Thanks for sending a request! hope you like your new pals ^~^

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.

summary: It takes a Mina to accept that Red must return to Kanto for a week every few months to pick fights with his fellow legends...
caption:
It takes a Mina to accept that Red must return to Kanto for a week every few months to pick fights with his fellow legends

—————————————

Mina: He really thought we’d be upset with him… For all that good discipline talk Baloo was throwing around I’m 80% sure she’s let Keahi off the hook by now
Red: To be honest, I’m sure she was through being mad at him before they even got home. But we aren’t mad at him right? You didn’t just say it was ok so he could sleep?
Mina: No, I meant it. I can’t be upset with him… He apologized and really truly feels bad about it along with realizing it could have been so much worse.
Red: Yeah… So~ How have things been this past week? Anything crazy happen?
Mina: I know with great certainty that Jas found a very shiny rock he wants to show you. Exciting hmm? How was Kanto?

Red: Very exciting, I’ll have to see it! I don’t want to talk about Kanto, I missed you and Jas all week.
Mina: Aww I’m touched~ Though we missed you too. Jas idolizes you so much, I’m sure he’s going to pick a Pichu so he can be just like his dad and his op Pikachu
Red: How can he possibly look up to me when he has you here all the time? Power and beauty all in one, the whole deal
Mina: Take the compliment you silly man >//u//>
Red: Nah ewe

It takes a Mina to accept that Red must return to Kanto for a week every few months to pick fights with his fellow legends

—————————————

Mina: He really thought we’d be upset with him… For all that good discipline talk Baloo was throwing around I’m 80% sure she’s let Keahi off the hook by now
Red: To be honest, I’m sure she was through being mad at him before they even got home. But we aren’t mad at him right? You didn’t just say it was ok so he could sleep?
Mina: No, I meant it. I can’t be upset with him… He apologized and really truly feels bad about it along with realizing it could have been so much worse.
Red: Yeah… So~ How have things been this past week? Anything crazy happen?
Mina: I know with great certainty that Jas found a very shiny rock he wants to show you. Exciting hmm? How was Kanto?

Red: Very exciting, I’ll have to see it! I don’t want to talk about Kanto, I missed you and Jas all week.
Mina: Aww I’m touched~ Though we missed you too. Jas idolizes you so much, I’m sure he’s going to pick a Pichu so he can be just like his dad and his op Pikachu
Red: How can he possibly look up to me when he has you here all the time? Power and beauty all in one, the whole deal
Mina: Take the compliment you silly man >//u//>
Red: Nah ewe
